> Install Legacy Raspberry Pi OS
   - [GUI] Update software
   - [GUI] Configure hostname
   - [GUI] Enable ssh, i2c, spi interfaces

> Configure VNC resolution by editting /boot/config.txt
   hdmi_force_hotplug=1
   hdmi_force_mode=1
   hdmi_drive=2
   hdmi_group=1
   hdmi_mode=16

> Setup password-less ssh from victory
   ssh-copy-id pi@gopigo.local

> Software
   - sudo apt-get install -y
     ack cmus elinks exa exuberant-ctags cscope fish flac git-lfs jack jq mc moc moc-ffmpeg-plugin
     mosh mpg321 ncdu neofetch pimixer powerline ranger ripgrep sd software-properties-common sox
     telnet tig tmux vim-nox wget xfce4-terminal
   - Install oh my fish
   - pip3 : evdev pyttsx3 selectors
   - manual
      + bashtop : https://github.com/aristocratos/bashtop
      + IOTstack : https://github.com/SensorsIot/IOTstack
      + PiKiss : https://github.com/jmcerrejon/PiKISS
      + bat : https://lindevs.com/display-contents-of-file-using-bat-on-raspberry-pi
      + ROS : http://wiki.ros.org/melodic/Installation/Ubuntu
      + Raspberry Pi Camera Web Interface : https://elinux.org/RPi-Cam-Web-Interface

> Install Dexter software from XWindows
   - Install software
      curl -kL dexterindustries.com/update_gopigo3 | bash
      curl -kL dexterindustries.com/update_sensors | bash
      curl -kL dexterindustries.com/update_brickpi3 | bash
      curl -kL dexterindustries.com/update_grovepi | bash
   - Calibrate black line and white line using the line-follower-calibration script
      + Need to modify the port in the Python script to AD1

> Install OpenCV (new)
   https://raspberrypi-guide.github.io/programming/install-opencv
   sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake pkg-config libjpeg-dev libtiff5-dev libjasper-dev libpng-dev libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev libswscale-dev libv4l-dev libxvidcore-dev libx264-dev libfontconfig1-dev libcairo2-dev libgdk-pixbuf2.0-dev libpango1.0-dev libgtk2.0-dev libgtk-3-dev libatlas-base-dev gfortran libhdf5-dev libhdf5-serial-dev libhdf5-103 python3-pyqt5 python3-dev -y
   sudo apt-get install python-opencv

> Increase swap space (for installing OpenCV the old way)
   - Temporarily stop swap
      sudo dphys-swapfile swapoff
   - Modify the size of the swap
      Add CONF_SWAPSIZE=2048 to /etc/dphys-swapfile
   - Initialize swap file
      sudo dphys-swapfile setup
   - Start swap
      sudo dphys-swapfile swapon

> Trick
   - Detect I2C devices
      sudo i2cdetect -y 1

   - Backup Raspberry Pi
   1) Mac OS X
      1.1) Backup
      diskutil list
      sudo dd bs=4M if=/dev/disk4 of=pi.img
      1.2) Restore
      diskutil unmountDisk /dev/disk4
      sudo ds bs=4m if=pi.img of=/dev/disk4
      diskutil eject /dev/disk4

   2) Linux
      2.1) Backup
      sudo dd bs=4M if=/dev/sdb1 of=pi.img
      sudo umount /dev/sdb1
      2.2) Restore
      sudo umount /dev/sdb1
      sudo dd bs=4M if=pi.img of=/dev/disk4
      sudo sync

--------------------------- Obsolete ---------------------------

> Install OpenCV
   # Note we need to increase the swap size on RP3B+ to 2048 and not to use make -j 4
   # otherwise, RP3B+ wil run out of memory.
   sudo apt-get install cmake
   sudo apt-get install libjpeg-dev libpng-dev libtiff-dev
   sudo apt-get install libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev libswscale-dev libv4l-dev
   sudo apt-get install libxvidcore-dev libx264-dev
   sudo apt-get install 'libgtk-3-dev libcanberra-gtk*'
   sudo apt-get install libatlas-base-dev gfortran
   mkdir opencv
   cd opencv
   git clone https://github.com/opencv/opencv.git
   git clone https://github.com/opencv/opencv_contrib.git
   cd opencv
   mkdir build
   cd build
   cmake -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr/local -D OPENCV_EXTRA_MODULES_PATH=/home/pi/workspace/opencv/opencv_contrib/modules ..
   make
   sudo make install
